text.__SUMMARY__: Acacia anarthros is a shrub of the genus Acacia and the subgenus Pulchellae. It is native to an area in the Wheatbelt region of Western Australia.The spinose shrub typically grows to a height of 0.1 to 0.5 metres (0.3 to 1.6 ft). It blooms from June to September and produces yellow flowers.
